tool.name: DesktopGateway

param.name: map_aoi
param.dialogReference: Polygon feature class used to define AOI layer.

param.name: map_name_field
param.dialogReference: Attribute field used to specify the map name.

param.name: map_template
param.dialogReference: The path to the map document that will be used to produce a complete map.

param.name: grid_xml
param.dialogReference: The XML grid definition template stores the specification's graphic properties for each grid layer.

param.name: export_type
param.expression: PDF | TIFF | JPEG | Multi-page PDF | Production PDF | Layout GeoTIFF | Map Package
param.dialogReference:
Indicates the type of export.

- PDF - Exports the map document to a PDF.

- TIFF - Exports the map document to a TIFF.

- JPEG - Exports the map document to a JPEG.

- Multi-page PDF - Exports the map documents to a Multi-page PDF.

- Production PDF - Exports the map document to a Production PDF.

- Layout GeoTIFF - Exports the map document to a Layout GeoTIFF.

- Map Package - Exports the map document to a Map Package.

param.name: working_directory
param.dialogReference: The working directory to which the tool writes export files.

param.name: production_pdf_xml
param.dialogReference: The path to the location of the Production PDF XML file.

param.name: production_workspace
param.dialogReference: The path to the location of the Production Database Workspace.

param.name: keep_mxd
param.dialogReference: Will keep a working copy of the map document that is generated for each area of interest.

tool.summary: A Map Generation python script has been provided to automate the output of cartographic products in various formats.This tool can be used to create maps over any map sheet extent. An area of interest (AOI) feature class is required for selecting the map sheet extents. This tool takes in the parameters, convert the variables to JSON, and calls the map generation logic.
tool.usage: This tool is desgined to be used from ArcGIS Desktop as a stand alone Python Tool.
